<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE COVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In her first speaking role, Marlee Matlin plays the hearing-impaired daughter 
of Lee Remick in "Bridge to Silence," a new CBS movie airing Sunday at 9 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
After Peggy Lawrence (Matlin) is injured in an auto accident that claims the 
life of her husband, she becomes involved in a tug-of-war with Marge (Remick) 
over the guardianship of Peggy's young daughter. 
</P>
<P>
Michael O'Keefe portrays a longtime friend who persuades Peggy that her return 
to the Theatre of the Deaf would be beneficial as therapy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, Marlee Matlin and Lee Remick Steve Fontanini / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
