<HEADLINE>
<P>
EMPIRE OF THE OLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I hope I never reach the age when I look forward to reading AARP's mindless 
magazine, Modern Maturity. AARP claims to be interested in the economics of us 
old folks, but when I sent for an insurance quote from a company they endorsed, 
I found it to be $1,000 a year more than I now pay. 
</P>
<P>
If AARP is my salvation for old age, I'll just continue on my own, thanks. 
</P>
<P>
WILLIAM H. WILLIAMS 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
