<HEADLINE>
<P>
YOU'LL TAKE GOOD RIBBING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Got a hankerin' for a slab o' ribs? 
</P>
<P>
Angelena's Kitchen Table, 4515 Sepulveda Blvd., Sherman Oaks. (818) 788-0465. 
Style: Not ordering the ribs would be a sin. Setting: Solid soul -- soul music, 
soul celeb photos and soul food. Recommended: Granddaddy's BBQ pork ribs. Cost 
per person: $9.75. 
</P>
<P>
Carl's BBQ, 5953 W. Pico Blvd., Los Angeles. (213) 934-0637. Style: Take-out 
ribs for that gnawing hunger. Setting: Mini-mall melange. Recommended: Pork 
ribs. Cost per person: $7.75. 
</P>
<P>
Dr. Hogly Woglys Tyler, Texas Bar-B-Que, 8136 Sepulveda Blvd., Van Nuys. (818) 
780-6701. Style: Texas-style barbecue for the extremely hungry. Setting: Bare 
bones. Recommended: Beef ribs. Cost per person: $8.95. 
</P>
<P>
Miller's Acorn, 23360 Lake Manor Drive, Chatsworth. (818) 888-2099. Style: 
Italian-American macho for garlic lovers. Setting: Rural roadhouse. 
Recommended: Baby back ribs. Cost per person: $12. 
</P>
<P>
Rosies BBQ Grillery, 11845 W. Olympic Blvd., Los Angeles. (213) 473-8533. (Also 
located in Northridge and Sherman Oaks.) Style: Mesquite-grilled ribs for 
non-foodies. Setting: New Southwestern pretty. Recommended: Spicy Southern 
spare ribs. Cost per person: $10.25. Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
