<HEADLINE>
<P>
66 DRUG RUNNERS, 4 BURGLARS HANGED IN IRANIAN CRACKDOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NICOSIA, Cyprus 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sixty-six drug smugglers and four burglars have been hanged in Tehran and 19 
other cities, state radio reported. 
</P>
<P>
The executions last week bring the total number of reported executions of drug 
smugglers in recent months to 379. 
</P>
<P>
The Tehran radio broadcast, monitored in Nicosia, said 17 of the smugglers were 
hanged in the capital. 
</P>
<P>
Several of those executed were also convicted of armed resistance, gun 
smuggling, "mischief, creating panic and involvement in murder," the radio 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities also confiscated 18,935 pounds of opium, 1,757 pounds of heroin and 
16,440 pounds of morphine from the smugglers, the radio reported. 
</P>
<P>
A Draconian new law that took effect Jan. 21 carries the death sentence for 
possession of even small quantities of drugs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
