<HEADLINE>
<P>
WILLIAM C. PAYETTE; LONGTIME EXECUTIVE WITH UPI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
William C. Payette, 75, a longtime executive with United Press International 
and United Features Syndicate who headed UPI's Los Angeles bureau in the 1940s. 
Payette, after joining United Press in 1936, established the first radio 
Teletype delivery of news to South America and the first daily overseas 
transmission of news pictures. He also organized Movietone News. In Dallas on 
Thursday of cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
