<HEADLINE>
<P>
W. BERLIN MAYOR URGED TO EASE TRAVEL LIMITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EAST BERLIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
East German dissidents want West Berlin's new mayor to urge East Germany to 
ease travel restrictions. 
</P>
<P>
"No progressive politician in the world should tolerate that in the middle of 
the safest zone of peace in the world, in Europe, people have to live walled 
in," they said in a letter to the Social Democrat mayor, Walter Momper. 
</P>
<P>
The letter, which asks Momper to raise the subject of travel in planned talks 
with East German leader Erich Honecker, was made available to reporters last 
week. 
</P>
