spotlight Universal and Disney studios' investment in Orlando, Fla. ; Photo, 
Orlando Mayor Bill Frederick says that someday the city will become the 
Hollywood of the East. TOM BURTON; Photo, A signature of the times: Daryl 
Hannah's autograph in Orlando. ; Photo, Ted Kaye, Disney's vice president for 
Orlando studio operations: "There's still a level of genuineness here, 
contrasted with some of the cynicism you find in L.A." ; Photo, Orlando is very 
aggressive in seeking movies business with ads such as this. ; Photo, COLOR, 
(Cover) Disney's Florida re-creation of Hollywood's Chinese Theater as it was 
in earlier days. 
</P>
