<HEADLINE>
<P>
TREATMENT OF ROGERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a retired United States Navy officer, I want to remind the parents and staff 
at La Jolla Country Day School that there's a price for freedom. And the 
prerequisites are courage, honor and a deep respect for the well-being of your 
fellow man. 
</P>
<P>
Mr. Burns, these are not qualities which a public relations firm can provide 
you. However, you can admit you made a mistake and return Sharon Rogers to her 
fourth-grade class. 
</P>
<P>
I can't think of a better way of teaching our kids that our freedom is worth 
preserving. 
</P>
<P>
CAPT. FRANK HOFFMAN (Ret.) 
</P>
<P>
Coronado 
</P>
</TEXT>
