<P>
The managing editor of a major Turkish newsmagazine went into hiding last month 
after being sentenced to nine years in jail for articles carried by the leftist 
publication, friends said. Fatma Yazici, 33, managing editor of the weekly 
Toward 2000, was charged with producing Communist and Kurdish propaganda, 
insulting Islam and being disrespectful to the president. The magazine has 
constantly been in trouble with authorities for tackling taboo subjects that 
often lead to prosecution under the country's restrictive press law. 
