<TEXT>
<P>
Return of billions of dollars in paid Medicare claims is being sought by the 
Health and Human Services and Justice departments. A spokesman for HHS 
Inspector General Richard P. Kusserow told the Washington Post that in many 
cases the law clearly makes private insurance companies liable for payment of 
patient claims for a number of employed persons over 65; but often the 
companies failed to pay bills, leaving them to Medicare. Louis B. Hays, acting 
administrator of Medicare, told the Post that underpayments over the last six 
years by private insurance companies may total several billion dollars. 
