<P>
Bottle-throwing demonstrators clashed with police at a rally of the right-wing 
Republican Party in central West Germany. A police spokesman said 17 people, 
including two police officers, were injured and seven demonstrators were 
arrested during the fighting in Grossostheim. About 1,400 people attended the 
demonstration, which was organized by an anti-rightist group that accuses the 
Republicans of being neo-fascist. The Republican Party, campaigning to stop a 
growing influx of political asylum-seekers into West Germany, won an unexpected 
7.5% of the vote in January's elections for the West Berlin city parliament. 
