<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEARCH CONTINUES FOR 6 REMAINING JAIL ESCAPEES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DEDHAM, Mass. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 200 police using helicopters and dogs searched Saturday for six inmates 
who fled a jail by sawing through the bars on a window and shimmying over a 
razor-sharp fence. 
</P>
<P>
The inmates escaped in a group of 13 Friday night from the Norfolk County House 
of Correction. Two were quickly captured, and five others were caught Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Overcrowding and racial tensions have fueled several outbreaks at the prison 
recently, officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
