<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHOOTINGS LEAVE 13-YEAR-OLD BOY DEAD, 9 INJURED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL J. YBARRA, Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LOS ANGELES 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nine people, including a woman pushing a baby stroller and a family leaving a 
convenience store, were among the wounded in a spate of shootings that also 
left a 13-year-old boy who was playing with a shotgun dead, police said 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Angelina Rojas, 31, and her daughters Maria, 6, and Bertha, 7, were wounded 
Friday at a 7-Eleven store in Long Beach when the store's clerk fired at a 
customer who had allegedly threatened him, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The clerk, Aoina Uiagalelei, surrendered to police hours later and was booked 
on suspicion of assault with a deadly weapon, Lt. Melvin Galwas said. 
</P>
<P>
Rojas and her children and the customer targeted by Uiagalelei, Robin Byrd, 32, 
were treated at a local hospital and released. 
</P>
<P>
Maria Guerrero, 27, was wounded in the arm Friday as she pushed a stroller 
carrying her 1-year-old baby and her 3-year-old child on Van Nuys Boulevard in 
Pacoima, police said. 
</P>
<P>
A witness said the suspects were shooting at a passing vehicle allegedly 
carrying rival street gang members when they hit Guerrero, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Guerrero was treated at Pacifica Hospital of the Valley in Sun Valley and 
released. The children were not injured. 
</P>
<P>
Officers arrested Herman Robinson, 19, of Pacoima on suspicion of assault with 
a deadly weapon. A second suspect remained at large. 
</P>
<P>
In other incidents: 
</P>
<P>
* Jonathan Baron, 36, of Redondo Beach was shot and critically wounded as he 
walked to his car inside a parking structure on Hawthorne Boulevard in 
Torrance, Lt. Mike Tamble said. Baron was listed in critical condition at 
UCLA-Harbor General Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
* A 17-year-old boy was in critical condition Saturday after being wounded in 
the head in a gang-related drive-by shooting in Boyle Heights. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was standing with five to eight fellow gang members in front of a 
party at a home in the 200 block of North Chicago Street when members of a 
rival gang drove by and gang slogans were shouted from the car, Los Angeles 
Police Detective Larry Martinez said. No arrests had been made Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
* A 13-year-old boy died after being accidentally shot in the back while he and 
three friends were playing with a loaded shotgun in a house in Watts, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Antoine Pierce, who lived in the Nickerson Gardens housing project, died at 
Martin Luther King Jr./Drew Medical Center. While one boy was holding the gun, 
it discharged and Pierce was fatally wounded, police said. 
</P>
<P>
* A 21-year-old man was shot in the buttocks as he tried to run from gang 
members at Gladstone's for Fish, a popular seafood restaurant in Pacific 
Palisades. 
</P>
<P>
* On Saturday afternoon, an unidentified ice cream man was shot in the abdomen 
and drove his truck to a South-Central Los Angeles police station for help, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The 42-year-old driver was shot by two men at 104th Street and Broadway, Sgt. 
Lon Salzman said. He was scheduled to undergo surgery at King Hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
