<P>
NORTHRIDGE MEN FALL IN VOLLEYBALL FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite 43 kills by senior middle blocker Bob Samuelson, Cal State Northridge 
was defeated by Indiana-Purdue-Ft. Wayne, 13-15, 16-14, 15-7, 4-15, 15-7, in 
the final of the Ball State men's volleyball tournament at Muncie, Ind., on 
Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
Neil Coffman added 25 kills for Northridge (10-19), which plays host to 
top-ranked UCLA on Monday night. Coffman and Samuelson were named to the 
all-tournament team. IPFW is 21-7. 
</P>
