<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: SDSU SWEEPS DOUBLEHEADER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego State's baseball team swept a Western Athletic Conference 
doubleheader from New Mexico, 10-3 and 11-2, Saturday in Albuquerque. The 
Aztecs improved to 23-13, 7-3. The Lobos fell to 7-20-1, 3-3. 
</P>
<P>
SDSU's Brian Dunn had three RBIs on a single, two triples and a home run in the 
first game. The second baseman could have hit for the cycle, but he stretched a 
double into his second triple in his final at-bat. Dunn went two for five with 
a double and a triple in the second game. 
</P>
<P>
Rob Brown (6-4) and Dave Riddle (3-0) were the winning pitchers. 
</P>
<P>
The University of San Diego lost both games of a West Coast Athletic Conference 
doubleheader to Loyola Marymount in Los Angeles. The Lions (20-17-1, 5-1) won 
by scores of 10-5 and 8-0. 
</P>
<P>
The second game was interrupted by a bench-clearing brawl in the first inning 
when USD starter Tony Battilega hit Rob Cannon with a pitch and Cannon charged 
the mound. Both were ejected, and USD protested the game. 
</P>
<P>
USD's Chuck Graham set a school record with his 53rd career double in the first 
game. Andy Asaro had 52 from 1979-82. 
</P>
<P>
Azusa Pacific swept Point Loma Nazarene College (17-18, 4-8 in the Golden State 
Athletic Conference), 5-0 and 23-2, at Azusa Pacific (21-12, 9-3). 
</P>
<P>
Cal Poly Pomona defeated U.S. International, 11-10, after the Gulls (13-26) had 
rallied to tie the score after trailing early, 8-0. 
</P>
<P>
Starters J.J. Fisher (4-1) and Mike Morgan (4-6) picked up victories as UC San 
Diego swept a doubleheader from Cal State San Bernardino, 10-5 and 6-4, in La 
Jolla. 
</P>
<P>
VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State's Eric Etebari had 34 kills to lead the Aztecs (13-14) over 
Pepperdine, 7-15, 15-8, 15-7, 7-15, 15-11 in a Western Intercollegiate 
Volleyball Assn. match at Peterson Gym. 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
University of San Diego's Lisa Ziomkowski pitched every inning and won both 
games of a doubleheader over Whittier, 10-3 and 5-3. USD is 17-20. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
UC San Diego swept its doubles matches and defeated Loyola Marymount, 6-3, in a 
nonconference match in La Jolla. 
</P>
<P>
TRACK AND FIELD 
</P>
<P>
The Point Loma Nazarene men (3-1) defeated Pomona Pitzer (4-2), 96-65. The 
Crusaders' Tommy Anderberg won the javelin (157-3), the shotput (45-4) and the 
discus (150-9). 
</P>
