<HEADLINE>
<P>
LETTER'S EFFECT ON OLD ACQUAINTANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re the letter by Dr. William Moss (April 2): 
</P>
<P>
We came to Santa Ana 33 years ago, the same year as Moss. We knew him then as a 
fine general surgeon who practiced high quality life-saving medicine. He later 
chose to limit his practice to life-preventing medicine (performing tubal 
ligations and vasectomies), and now he is specializing in life-destroying 
procedures. It saddens us to know that he is the face and name behind the 
Tustin abortion clinic. 
</P>
<P>
His letter of thanks to the Tustin police and the pro-choice advocates who were 
at his clinic to "protect" him and his patients has made us even more aware 
that those of us who are advocates of the pro-life cause -- which holds that 
all human life is sacred and has dignity and value -- must become more vocal 
and visible. 
</P>
<P>
It seems abortionists have protectors, animals have protectors, even car owners 
are told by an American manufacturer that "protection is your right." Only 
human babies not yet born are unprotected. 
</P>
<P>
Dr. JOHN McANDREW 
</P>
<P>
THERESE McANDREW 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 
</P>
