<P>
FREDERICKS SPRINTS PAST WATTS IN USC MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Frank Fredericks of Brigham Young outfinished USC freshman Quincy Watts to win 
both sprints in the USC Centennial Invitational track meet Saturday at Cromwell 
Field. 
</P>
<P>
Fredericks was clocked in 10.39 seconds in the 100 meters and in a hand-timed 
20.5 in the 200, while Watts ran 10.62 and 20.7. 
</P>
<P>
USC's Michelle Taylor won the women's 200 and 400 meters and anchored both 
winning relay teams as the Trojan women beat BYU in a meet that was decided by 
the final event -- the 1,600-meter relay. 
</P>
