<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOOROS AND DONALD STILL TIED FOR LEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HATTIESBURG, Miss. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jim Booros and Mike Donald shot four-under-par 66s Saturday to continue sharing 
the lead in the $200,000 Deposit Guaranty golf tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The two players, close friends off the course, were at 199 after 54 holes on 
the Hattiesburg Country Club's 6,280-yard course. 
</P>
<P>
"I would rather play with a friend like this," Booros said. "Mike said a few 
things that relaxed me." 
</P>
<P>
Robert Thompson, David Peoples and Fred Funk shot 65s, and Lance Ten Broeck, 
who was in third place by himself going into the round, had a 67. All were at 
201. 
</P>
<P>
P.H. Horgan III, whose 64 was the day's best round was at 202 with Steve Lowery 
and Bob Wolcott. Lowery shot a 65 and Wolcott a 66. 
</P>
<P>
Donald, third at the Woodlands last week after leading for three rounds, 
started fast Saturday with three straight birdies. 
</P>
<P>
He dropped back with bogeys on the sixth and ninth holes but made three more 
birdies on the back nine. 
</P>
<P>
Booros, who has held or shared the lead in all three rounds here, had an 
eagle-3 on the 482-yard third hole and a fine save for par at No. 6. 
</P>
<P>
He birdied Nos. 11 and 13, had a bogey at the 15th and finished with a birdie 
on the 18th. The bogey was only his second of the tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
