<TEXT>
<P>
Kevin O'Neill, who earned a reputation as one of the nation's top basketball 
recruiters during three years as an assistant at Arizona, was named coach at 
Marquette. 
</P>
<P>
O'Neill, 32, replaces Bob Dukiet, who was fired in March after three tumultuous 
seasons marked by player-coach conflicts and a 39-46 record, including 
Marquette's first consecutive losing seasons in 24 years. 
