<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTY'S CHOICE OF MCDONALD'S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Surprised, amazed, dumbfounded, shocked and annoyed are just a few of my 
reactions to the county board's "unanimous" selection of McDonald's as the 
fast-food concessionaire for the new airport facility ("Ronald McDonald Beats 
Out Carl's Jr. for Airport Space," March 29). I thought that we deserved 
better, much better! The best that can be said about McDonald's is that they 
are consistent: consistently bland and unimaginative with a limited menu that 
hasn't changed appreciably in years. McDonald's has continually promoted their 
limited menu with heavy advertising and hype aimed at the very young. All hype 
and nothing new just about sums up McDonald's marketing approach. 
</P>
<P>
As a member of a large group of "full-fare" business travelers already paying a 
premium to fly in and out of John Wayne Airport, I was expecting a much better 
fast-food restaurant such as Carl's Jr. Certainly an Orange County-based 
concessionaire with a much more diverse menu, offering higher quality 
selections would have been a better choice. 
</P>
<P>
I certainly hope that the Orange County Board of Supervisors reconsiders its 
decision on this matter. At the very least, please offer us a choice by 
splitting the fast-food concession between McDonald's and Carl's Jr. 
</P>
<P>
ROGER D. GIBB 
</P>
<P>
Irvine 
</P>
</TEXT>
