TRAVEL NEWS AND BRIEFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A slide-discussion on Russia and Scandinavia will be held by the Bon Voyage 
Travel Club at 7:45 p.m. on April 21 at the Community Room, 9696 Wilshire 
Blvd., Beverly Hills. Admission $5. For more information, call (213) 476-4869. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
Mort Loveman, travel photographer and lecturer will offer a free slide lecture 
on Kenya and Tanzania safari at 1 p.m. Wednesday at the Roxbury Park Club 
House, 471 S. Roxbury Drive, Beverly Hills. For more information, call (213) 
550-4761. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
European travel on a budget will be the topic of an American Youth Hostel (AYH) 
seminar at 1 p.m. Saturday at the AYH Travel Centre, 335 W. 7th St, San Pedro. 
Admission $3. For more information, call (213) 831-8846. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
More than 400 power and sailboats plus marine accessory and service exhibits 
will be part of the 16th Annual Newport Boat Show Wednesday through April 16 at 
Lido Marina Village, Newport Beach. Show hours are 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. weekdays 
and 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. weekends. Free parking will be available off Tustin and 
Avon Avenues in Newport Beach with complimentary shuttle to Lido Marina Village 
every 15 minutes. Admission $5 for adults, $2 for children 6 to 12 and children 
under 6 free. For additional information, call (714) 673-9360. 
</P>
<P>
