<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOBIL GUIDES FOR BUDGET TRAVELERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 1989 Mobil Travel Guide "Lodgings for Less" steers budget-minded travelers 
to clean, comfortable and highly rated accommodations throughout the United 
States and Canada. Average price per night for two is about $50. (As rooms for 
less than $50 are scarce in some areas, the guide also lists more costly 
lodgings when necessary.) 
</P>
<P>
Information is contained in three compact regional volumes covering major 
cities and resort areas in the South, Northeast/Midwest (plus Canada) and West 
(plus Canada). Published by Prentice Hall, each volume retails at bookstores 
and other outlets for $5.95. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA040989-0222 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 42022 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
April 9, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Travel; Part 7; Page 22; Column 2; Travel Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
303 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOME TIPS FOR THE TRAVELING FAMILY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Some family traveling tips from the Automobile Assn. of America: 
</P>
<P>
Suggested budget for a family of four -- two adults and two children -- is $168 
a day for lodging and meals, plus $8 per 100 miles for gas, oil, tires and 
maintenance (with a car averaging 23 miles a gallon). 
</P>
<P>
The average cost for lodging is $78 a night, based on the rates charged by 
approved accommodations listed in AAA TourBooks. This rate includes $5 nightly 
per child. However, if children are within an age limit set by the management, 
usually up to 14, there may not be an extra charge. 
</P>
<P>
Families traveling in Southern California probably will spend a little more 
than the national average, according to AAA figures. The average cost of 
lodging will be $10 to $15 more and gas prices probably will be about $5 more. 
This adds up to an average daily cost of $188 for a family of four traveling in 
Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
Vacation spending depends on a family's preferences and means, but costs vary 
by area. Higher rates can be expected in large metropolitan areas and at 
resorts in season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
