<P>
An agreement to gradually transfer ownership of a 5,360-acre preserve of oak 
groves and canyon lands to the county will be discussed Tuesday by the Board of 
Supervisors. The area, known as Limestone Canyon, is currently owned by the 
Irvine Co. and is east of Irvine and north of the El Toro Marine Corps Air 
Station. 
</P>
